Born Aug. 3, 1804, at Fair Haven, Bristol Co., Massachusetts, to J. and N. Bennett. Presented as assistant president with the First Presidency April 8, 1841, at age 36 (See History of the Church 4:341); disfellowshipped May 25, 1842; excommunicated latter part of 1842; died Aug. 5, 1867, in Polk City, Polk Co., Iowa at age 63.